cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.SY 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it deals with the concept of learning to optimize using data-driven algorithms. It also involves the development of a novel solution, Rover Descent, which is a machine learning algorithm. 

It could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as the paper deals with the development of a policy that can optimize over classes of functions. 

cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) is another likely sub-category as the paper involves the use of machine learning algorithms to optimize numerical criteria. 

cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is a possible sub-category as the paper involves the optimization of high-dimensional landscapes, which could be related to computer vision tasks. 

Finally, cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with the development of a navigation policy on a partially observable loss surface, which could be related to control systems.
